# Video files — never commit footage.
# Git keeps binaries in history forever, even after deletion. The spike clip is
# 68 MB of personal footage and is fully replaceable: drop any clip into
# spike/media/ and regenerate (see spike/README.md).
*.mp4
*.MP4
*.mov
*.MOV
*.m4v
*.mxf
*.braw

# Node
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Expo / React Native (for when the app lands)
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
*.xcuserstate

# Generated native project (Continuous Native Generation). Everything native is
# authored in app.config.ts and modules/frame-player/; ios/ is reproduced by
# `expo prebuild -p ios` (see SETUP.md). Not committed because the generated
# Info.plist embeds the real OAuth URL scheme, and this repo is public.
ios/

